author: andreasmyth
msg: Create gzipped (gnu) tar files when building distributions on Unix.
The contents of the these is identical to the zip archives created on
Windows except that ALL files in the bin directory are now adjusted to local
concentions and that on UNIX they have execute permissions.
Note that the file name lengths of some files exceeds the limit for tar
and therefore may require the use of gnu tar to perform the extraction.
